image could&#39;ve been generated naturally.

Remember the old days when TV&#39;s had tuning knobs?  You could adjust it so 
you had the best picture. Or tune it completely off-channel.  Modern ones 
just don&#39;t work that way.

Somewhere in my junquebox I still have an ancient UHF converter from the 
early days of UHF, when most TV&#39;s didn&#39;t have it.  You set your TV to 
channel 2, I believe, and turned a knob on the front to tune in UHF 
stations.

Zack

